177
00:21:25,530 --> 00:21:34,065
To put it in a somewhat simplified way, there are two basic attitudes discernible in the history of religions.

178
00:21:34,510 --> 00:21:41,368
On the one hand, there is the pagan cosmos, the divine hierarchical order of cosmic principles,

179
00:21:41,830 --> 00:21:51,503
which, when copied onto society, gives the image of a congruent edifice in which each member is at its own place.

180
00:21:52,690 --> 00:21:56,768
The supreme good is here, the global balance of principles,

181
00:21:57,290 --> 00:22:01,428
and evil stands for their derailment or derangement,

182
00:22:01,970 --> 00:22:07,126
for the excessive assertion of one principle to the detriment of others,

183
00:22:07,590 --> 00:22:13,727
of the masculine to the detriment of the feminine, of reason to the detriment of feeling, and so on.

184
00:22:14,310 --> 00:22:18,105
The cosmic balance is then reestablished through the work of justice,

185
00:22:18,450 --> 00:22:27,224
which with inexorable necessity sets things straight again by crushing the derailed element.

186
00:22:28,230 --> 00:22:37,968
With regard to the social body, an individual is good when he or she acts in accordance with his special place within the social edifice,

187
00:22:38,330 --> 00:22:44,727
when he respects nature which provides food and shelter, when he shows respect for his superiors,

188
00:22:45,270 --> 00:22:54,107
when he takes care of his followers or children in a fatherly way and so on and so on.

189
00:22:54,530 --> 00:23:05,288
And evil is defined as, evil occurs when some particular strata or individuals are no longer satisfied with their proper place.

190
00:23:05,710 --> 00:23:14,725
Children no longer obey parents, servants no longer obey masters, rulers no longer take care of their subjects and so on and so on.

191
00:23:16,513 --> 00:23:24,088
I think that this is the ethics which even now is re-emerging often in the guise of some New Age wisdom.

192
00:23:24,451 --> 00:23:33,167
It's called so-called holistic approach, you know, every element should remain at its proper place, evil is imbalanced and so on and so on.

193
00:23:34,050 --> 00:23:38,206
I claim that Christianity does precisely the opposite.

194
00:23:39,210 --> 00:23:54,288
Christianity introduces into the global balanced order a principle totally foreign to it, a The principle that, measured by the standards of a traditional cosmology, cannot but appear as a monstrous distortion.

195
00:23:55,210 --> 00:24:02,170
The principle according to which each individual has an immediate access to the universality.

196
00:24:02,711 --> 00:24:09,969
In Christianity, the universality of the Holy Spirit, or today, the universality of human rights, freedoms, and so on.

197
00:24:10,711 --> 00:24:18,789
I can participate in this universal dimension directly, irrespective of my special place within the global social order.

198
00:24:20,333 --> 00:24:25,949
